The Dental Hygiene program at the college is accredited by the Commission on Dental Accreditation of Canada. Graduates of this program are eligible to apply for the National Dental Hygiene Certification Examination and, upon successful completion, can register with the College of Dental Hygienists of Ontario (CDHO) to practice in the province. The program is a six-semester course with field experience starting from semester 1. In semesters 1 and 2, students practice on manikins. From semesters 3 to 6, they progressively treat real clients both at the college's on-site WAVE Dental Clinic and off-site with various community partners. The clinic has over 75 dental chairs, additional chairs with x-ray facilities, and 24 enclosed dental suites equipped for aerosol generating procedures. Students learn to provide care across the lifespan, treating clients with various oral health needs. Interested students who need more competitive marks can enroll in the Pre-Health Sciences Pathway to Advanced Diplomas and Degrees (A108) program. Travel to off-site placement sites may be required, and clinical hours include early mornings that extend into the evening.

Graduates are eligible to apply for the National Dental Hygiene Certification Examination, which is a requirement for registration by the College of Dental Hygienists of Ontario to practice in Ontario. 4. Analyze oral health issues in need of advocacy and identify networks to support change.

6. Establish and maintain professional and interprofessional relationships that contribute to client care safety and positive outcomes.
